# No Mock Data — Always Real Data

**Rule: Never use mock or placeholder data in the Portal.** All UI must be wired to real APIs and real data.

## Do

- Use data from props/API only; show empty states when there is no data.
- Derive stats (counts, totals, upcoming) from real lists when the API doesn’t return them.
- Normalize API shapes (e.g. `schedules`, `next_schedule`) inside components or selectors for display.
- On API/load errors, show error state and optionally retry; do not fall back to fake data.

## Do Not

- Add or keep `mock*` arrays, `showMockData` props, or DEV-only mock fallbacks.
- Use hardcoded demo data to fill lists, stats, or activity feeds.
- Return mock suggestions or placeholder results from hooks (e.g. SEO generation) when the API fails.

## Commerce panels

- **EventsPanel**, **ServicesPanel**, **ProductsPanel**, **ClassesPanel**: receive real `events`/`services`/`products`/`classes` and optional `stats`; derive stats from lists when not provided; show “No … yet” when empty.
- **RecentActivity**, **CommerceMetrics**: receive real `activity`/`metrics`; show “No recent activity” / “No metrics available” when empty.
